This readme will help you install the new Gui from linav project. This Gui is really beta, this mean some things
won't work all the time. But it can't do anything to your av.

All you need to do to install it is to copy all files from the package to the root folder of av's hard disk.
Install a bootloader like the one from avos or winav or avlo. (avlo is provided in this package) 
Launch the file called linux.bin.

Be sure to have linux.bin and myinit in the root folder of the hard disk and also the avwm folder.

At the end of linux boot the gui will automatically be stated. You'll see a menu with some plugins.
To view, text, images and hear mp3, use the browser. Menu can be called from plugins useing F3 key.
